ce:section.ce:para:
To assess the accumulation of 99mTc-GQDs–pembrolizumab in tumor tissues, SPECT scans were conducted on mice bearing 4T1 tumors, one hour following the intravenous injection of 7.4 MBq of the radiotracer (as shown in Fig. 9
                        ). The SPECT images clearly demonstrated a high level of uptake of 99mTc-GQDs–pembrolizumab (8.4 %ID/g) in the tumor area. In addition, SPECT scans were also performed on normal mice injected with 99mTc-GQDs–pembrolizumab, revealing significant accumulation of the radiotracer in the liver. The biodistribution profile of 99mTc-GQDs–pembrolizumab, acquired two hours post-injection into the tail vein of 4T1 tumor-bearing mice, was presented in Fig. 10
                        . These results provided valuable insight into the distribution and accumulation of the radiotracer in various tissue and organs, emphasizing the potential of the developed nanoparticle-antibody conjugate for targeted imaging applications.
